[1]
Date: Sat 25 Jun 2005
From: Dan Silver <dsilver@reedpointgroup.com>
Source: XinHuaNet.com [edited]
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2005-06/25/content_3136079.htm>


Ministry: plague in Tibet brought under control
-----------------------------------------------
The plague in Zhongba, a county in Xigaze Prefecture of south west China's
Tibet Autonomous Region, has been brought under control, the Chinese
Ministry of Health cited a report of the Tibet Department of Health as
saying. The epidemic has so far affected 5 people, an official with the
ministry said here on Sat 25 Jun 2005. The disease came over them during
the period 13 to 18 Jun 2005, and 2 of them died.

The official stated that, after the epidemic occurred, health organizations
in the Tibet autonomous region immediately launched an epidemiology probe
in an effort to track down and quarantine the people who had had direct
contact with the patients, to oblige them to take preventive medicines, as
well as taking other disease prevention and control measures, including
sterilization and quarantine.

After receiving report of the epidemic, the ministry also immediately sent
experts to the epidemic area to help cope with it. The ministry reported
the epidemic to the WHO early Saturday morning, 25 Jun 2005. Meanwhile, the
ministry asked the epidemic areas to beef up publicity about prevention and
to urge local people to report suspect cases to health departments as soon
as possible.

--
Dan Silver
<dsilver@reedpointgroup.com>

